		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=QuazarJD&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Great experience for druid is Pet killing.&nbsp;&nbsp;I used to like PoN (stalkers prefered cuz of 1k per hour vendor loot) but anything will go.  Grab a raven (and if you are high enough there are high level ravens that hit for 300+ instead of the 260).  Snare, Debuff, Charm, Nine(or whatever), Strenght, Regen, DS.  Pull a mob(I prefer more to ease the boredom) with snare/root.  Sick pet on it.  Do at least a little damage yourself on it, if you dont then the experience is cut way back.  Then sit there and CH your pet.  Get Cha over a 100, although others say it doesnt help.  I say BS.  <br><br>This will do two things for you at the high end.  Teach you how to manage agro and teach you how to heal.<br><br>Tip:  If you pet is gonna die then invis yourself.  Regroup.  Recover pet and heal it up before reengaging.<br><br>Exp is way better then kiting anything else (well until EP or the locked zones in future expansions.)<br><br><br>There is another tactic on rotating your pet.  I dont like it at all, but I didnt really give it a chance.<br><br>Peace (and quit stealing my camps)<br><br>Another zone is PoStorm.  The forest frogs( as they are called on my server).  I didnt like this camp much for 3 reasons.  1) camped all the time, 2) Exp wasnt that much better (because you have very limited supply of mobs), and 3) Loot sucks.<br><br><br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Sep 23 23:02:08 2004 by QuazarJD</span class="sm"></i></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="