		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.49]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=MiegreWindWalker&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I agree with Bromen and Quazar both ... to a point.&nbsp;&nbsp;HoH is great xp if you get a DC pet and quad around the gardens, but a pain when there are others doing the same thing, and slow to boot because they have a good deal of HP.<br><br>If you can, get a Mage to summon you one of their piercing weps that is fast (not really familiar with the best items there) along with the haste mask.  Then DC the pet, use pet haste and SoE it as well.  Then park it in the middle of the garden (pet guard) and go Harmony pull a single of the black-suited archway guards.  Have Immolation of Ro or better memmed and Snare at the least (a full set of DoTs would be even better if you have the mana to dish it out).  Snare then Immo the guard and begin kiting around the walls.  Immo should keep aggro on you along with dropping its AC and doing DoT damage as well.  This way, you can be sure the little Wrulan you have attacking it from behind will not suddenly get attacked and die quickly (they do not have much in the way of AC/HP even with a full set of armors and buffs so they die fast when attacked).<br><br>Drop DoTs on it and be sure to keep pet haste memmed so you can re-do it when it fades, which is too damn quick IMO.  Rinse, lather, repeat and you can get decent xp at it ... but just like the Elysians in UP when farming the armors, it takes quite a bit of time and patience if you are doing it alone.<br><br>----------------<br>As far as PoN goes, I agree with grabbing a raven, but kite the mobs like you do with the HoH guards or you will end up using a lot of mana healing.  DoTs take up much less mana and you can do damage at the same time the pet is.  If you are really lucky you can find a light-blue raven that you can DC, so keep a look out and grab it when you can so you do not need to worry about the hasted and buffed raven coming to kick yer butt when charm breaks (and they always seem to do it when you have adds, low mana, or when you are not paying attention, hehehe).<br><br>Hope that helps.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=687935" target="akztarg">Master Chef Miegre Nature'Dancer</a> - Natureguard on <a href="HTTP://forums.ayonae.ro" target="akztarg">Ayonae Ro</a>-- Proud Member of <a href="HTTP://www.fellowshipofdragons.com" target="akztarg">Fellowship of Dragons</a><br><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=688542" target="akztarg">Lidium</a> - Myrmidon of 59 seasons on Ayonae Ro<br><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=701495" target="akztarg">Miegromper</a> - 42nd season Pally on Ayonae Ro</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
